  <brief_title>A Phase II Study of Carboplatin Plus Irinotecan Versus Irinotecan in Children With Refractory Solid Tumors</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Bristol-Myers Squibb</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Bristol-Myers Squibb</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This clinical research study is being conducted to investigate the effectiveness of combining
      carboplatin and irinotecan, versus irinotecan alone, in treating children who have refractory
      solid tumors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
